Enough European Community (EC) statesappear to be opposed to the proposals by the EC Commission fora 330 European currency unit (Ecu) a tonne tax on vegetableoils, fats and marine oils to block adoption by EC ministers,British Farm Minister Michael Jopling said.    He told a news conference held during a meeting here of ECagriculture ministers that Britain, West Germany, theNetherlands, Denmark, and Portugal were all against the tax.    Between them, these five countries had more than enoughvotes in the weighted voting system used in EC ministers'meetings to block a decision, Jopling said. Reuter&#3;